3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and mark prices. The on-chain nature means funding payments are settled automatically through smart contracts with sub-second finality. Unlike CEXs, all funding calculations are transparent and verifiable on Hyperliquid's L1 blockchain. The 1-hour intervals provide more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to the standard 8-hour cycles on most exchanges."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","W","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"W/USDT represents an infrastructure play in the crypto ecosystem, often experiencing funding rate volatility during network development phases or partnership announcements. The smaller market cap and trading volume can lead to more pronounced funding rate swings compared to major tokens. Infrastructure tokens like W tend to have less predictable funding patterns, creating opportunities for skilled arbitrageurs."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"W/USDT funding rates on Hyperliquid have shown significant volatility, particularly during periods of infrastructure development announcements or broader DeFi market movements. The 1-hour funding intervals amplify these patterns, with rates often swinging from strongly positive to negative within short timeframes. Historical data suggests funding rates correlate with W's price momentum and overall market sentiment toward infrastructure tokens. Peak funding rate periods typically occur during major network upgrades or ecosystem expansions."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The combination of 1-hour funding intervals and W's volatility creates frequent arbitrage windows on Hyperliquid. Traders can capitalize on funding rate differentials between Hyperliquid and other exchanges trading W perpetuals. The on-chain order book provides transparent liquidity data, enabling precise entry and exit timing. Sub-second settlement means positions can be adjusted rapidly as funding rates shift, particularly important given the hourly reset schedule."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"W's smaller market cap introduces heightened price volatility risks that can offset funding rate profits if not properly hedged. The on-chain nature means gas costs (though minimal on Hyperliquid) should be factored into profit calculations for smaller position sizes. Liquidity can be limited during volatile periods, potentially affecting arbitrage exit strategies. The relatively new ecosystem also carries smart contract risks despite audited code, requiring careful position sizing for risk management."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are W/USDT funding rates updated on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding rates are calculated and settled every hour on Hyperliquid, providing 24 funding periods per day. This frequent settlement creates more arbitrage opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What makes W funding rates particularly volatile on Hyperliquid?","answer":"W's status as an infrastructure token combined with smaller trading volumes leads to more pronounced funding rate swings. The 1-hour intervals on Hyperliquid amplify these movements, creating both opportunities and risks for arbitrageurs."},{"question":"Can I verify funding rate calculations on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Yes, all funding rate calculations are transparent and verifiable on Hyperliquid's blockchain. The on-chain order book means you can independently verify the premium calculations used to determine funding rates."},{"question":"What are the main risks when arbitraging W/USDT funding rates?","answer":"Primary risks include W's price volatility potentially exceeding funding gains, limited liquidity during volatile periods, and the inherent smart contract risks of the relatively new Hyperliquid ecosystem. Proper hedging and position sizing are essential."}]}]
